# Make.com → Spectral Soundworks IG Reply Notifications

## Important: What Make.com Can Actually Do

> [!WARNING]
> Make.com's Instagram module does **not** have a native "Watch DMs" trigger (Meta removed it). The practical options through Make are:
> 1. **Custom Webhook from Meta directly** — Make acts as the receiver, you set up the Meta app
> 2. **Via Manychat** — Manychat captures DMs and fires a webhook to Make, which forwards to your app
> 3. **Watch Comments** — only works for comments on posts, not DMs
>
> **Recommended path: Use Make as a Webhook relay from Manychat.** It's the fastest zero-code option for DMs.

---

## Option A — Manychat → Make → Spectral (Recommended, ~30 min)

Manychat has a native Instagram DM integration and can fire HTTP requests when messages are received.

### Prerequisites
- [Manychat](https://manychat.com) account (free tier works)
- Instagram account connected to Manychat (Business or Creator + Facebook Page required)
- Your app publicly accessible (see "Expose Your App" below)

### Step 1 — Expose Your App

**For local dev (temporary):**
```bash
# Install ngrok
npm install -g ngrok

# In a new terminal, expose port 3000
ngrok http 3000
```
Copy the `https://xxxx.ngrok-free.app` URL — that's your public base URL.

**For production:** Use your deployed domain directly.

### Step 2 — Set Up Manychat

1. Go to [app.manychat.com](https://app.manychat.com) → Connect Instagram
2. Create a new **Flow** → trigger: **Instagram DM received**
3. Add an **External Request** action (HTTP POST) with:

   **URL:**
   ```
   https://YOUR_PUBLIC_URL/api/ig/reply
   ```

   **Method:** `POST`

   **Headers:**
   ```
   Content-Type: application/json
   X-Webhook-Secret: PhsGL0lGJOigNIxYro1ZFdpyTvG8OlZ0312BZadab+k=
   ```

   **Body:**
   ```json
   {
     "instagramHandle": "{{last_input_text}}",
     "messageText": "{{last_input_text}}",
     "secret": "PhsGL0lGJOigNIxYro1ZFdpyTvG8OlZ0312BZadab+k="
   }
   ```

   > [!NOTE]
   > In Manychat, use the variable picker to insert the actual field names:
   > - `instagramHandle` → use `{{contact.ig_username}}` (the artist's IG handle)
   > - `messageText` → use `{{last_input_text}}` (the message they sent)

4. Save and publish the flow.

