## Option B — Meta Webhook Directly into Make (More Setup, More Reliable)

If you want Make to receive the raw Meta webhook:

### Step 1 — Create a Make Scenario

1. New scenario → search **Webhooks** → **Custom Webhook**
2. Click **Add** → name it `ig-reply-receiver` → copy the webhook URL
3. Add a second module: **HTTP → Make a Request**

### Step 2 — Configure the HTTP Module

| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| URL | `https://YOUR_PUBLIC_URL/api/ig/reply` |
| Method | `POST` |
| Body type | `Raw` |
| Content type | `JSON (application/json)` |
| Request content | See below |

**Request body (mapping Make's webhook output):**
```json
{
  "instagramHandle": "{{1.entry[].messaging[].sender.username}}",
  "messageText": "{{1.entry[].messaging[].message.text}}",
  "secret": "PhsGL0lGJOigNIxYro1ZFdpyTvG8OlZ0312BZadab+k="
}
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Meta often sends only a numeric **sender ID**, not a username. If `sender.username` is blank, you'll need to add a lookup step — see "Sender ID Fallback" below.

### Step 3 — Register the Make Webhook with Meta

In the [Meta Developer Console](https://developers.facebook.com):
1. Create an App (type: Business)
2. Add **Instagram** product
3. Under Webhooks → Subscribe to `messages` events
4. Set callback URL to your Make webhook URL
5. Set verify token to any string (e.g., `spectral_verify`)

### Sender ID Fallback

If Make receives a numeric sender ID instead of a username, add a **HTTP module** between the webhook and your relay:

```
GET https://graph.facebook.com/v19.0/{{sender_id}}?fields=username&access_token={{page_access_token}}
```

Then map `{{username}}` into the `instagramHandle` field of the relay request.

---

## Verify It's Working

Once set up, send a test DM to your Instagram account from another account. You should see:

1. ✅ `POST /api/ig/reply` hit in your Next.js server logs
2. ✅ A new `REPLY_RECEIVED` Activity on the lead in the DB
3. ✅ Lead status updated: `CONTACTED → FOLLOW_UP`
4. ✅ 🔔 Novu bell badge in your sidebar

You can also test the notification side independently at any time:
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/ig/test-notification \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"artistName":"Test Artist","instagramHandle":"testartist","messageSnippet":"Yo this sounds great!"}'
```

---

## Quick Decision Guide

| Your situation | Use |
|---|---|
| Want it working today, no code | **Manychat → Make → `/api/ig/reply`** |
| Want it long-term, properly | **Meta Webhooks → Make → `/api/ig/reply`** |
| Want full control, no third party | **Meta Webhooks → `/api/ig/reply` directly** |

All three options POST to the same `/api/ig/reply` endpoint — the endpoint is already built and waiting.
